
// Kotlin Null Safety

String st = null

if(st == null) 0  else st.length //
it depends on you

# We can Declaring two types
 1.Nullable - We can assign null
 2.Non-Nullable - We can not assign null

 // Safe Call (?.) - it used to invoke a method(function,object) or access a property only it the receiver is non-null if receiver is null then result will be null
 // Elvis Operator (?:) - If found null then provide default value if you want

 // Safe Casts('as?') - it us for safe casting -
 // !! Operator (Non-null Assertion) -- Is used to tell the compiler that the receiver cannot be null. nullable convert into non- nullable value
 // Let Function -- execute block of code
 // Syntax   .let {}


